content:
Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools include Reports and Dashboards, Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards, CRM Analytics, Get Started Using CRM Analytics, Go Mobile with CRM Analytics, Set Up the CRM Analytics Platform.

Data Manager helps Get Started with Data Integration. Connect and Sync Your Data to CRM Analytics by Clean, Transform, and Load Data with Data Prep.

Data Prep Access Based on Your User Type allows Create a Recipe with Data Prep using Input Node: Add Data to the Recipe, Aggregate Node, Append Node: Stack Rows from Different Sets of Data, Filter Node: Filter Rows, Join Node: Add Related Columns of Data to the Recipe, Transform Node: Transform the Data Before Loading It Into a Target.

Transformations for Data Prep Recipes include Connect and Reorganize Nodes or Branches in a Recipe, Copy and Paste a Recipe, Keyboard Shortcuts for Building Data Prep Recipes, Preview Results in a Data Prep Recipe, Profile Columns to Understand Data in a Data Prep Recipe.

Limitations When Using Data Prep includes Manage Recipes by Run Data Sync and Recipes to Create and Refresh Datasets. Other Ways to Integrate Data include Get Started Faster with Data Templates, Manage Datasets, Data Integration Best Practices, Data Integration Troubleshooting.

Update Node: Swap Column Values allows swapping column values with data from another data source when key pairs match in CRM Analytics. In a Data Prep recipe, select the Add Node button and choose Update to update selected account names after acquisitions and mergers by replacing name from an uploaded spreadsheet based on matching account IDs.
title: Update Node in CRM Analytics for Data Swapping
